Doctor, I have read your input on a number of different topics.  Why do you persist to agitate and call names?  If this dialog is important to you, why do you continue to alienate those that you are having conversations with?  Other topics show that your dialogs are caring, concerned and offer insight to your opinions about your side of the discussions.  I said that I recognize you but don't accept your point of view and that was o.k. with you.  Why isn't it o.k. for others to reject those things that you hold so dear?  Why can't I or someone else have an opinion that differs from your appearance of the moral high ground?  Can't you accept that someone who is just out of high school, seventeen years old and from a cultural background differnet from yours that enlisting in the service is an honorable thing to do?  Can you accept that as an eighteen year old boy that they might not have the education, desire or even the understanding that this conflict was not a good thing?  Can you see that?  Can you see that at eighteen years old someone not seeing the politics involved?  Can you see that same person rejecting your political passions now that they are a little older and wiser? <br>
Can you understand that I personally take offense at being talked down to over the electronic media?  Can you understand the anger and outrage from the vets to have someone discount their service for this country?<br>
Or do you care?<br><br>
 
